chordpro:
{title: O Come, All Ye Faithful}
{subtitle: Adeste Fideles — English tr. Frederick Oakeley, 1841}
{key: G}
{time: 4/4}
{tempo: 88}
{comment: Pair with 神の御子は今宵しも (Japanese translation by 讃美歌 1903/1954 committee).}

{start_of_verse: 1}
[G]O come, all ye [D]faithful,
[Em]Joyful and tri[D]umphant!
[G]O come ye, O [C]come ye to [D]Bethle[G]hem;
[G]Come and be[D]hold Him
[Em]Born the King of [D]Angels:
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_chorus}
[G]O come, let us a[D]dore Him,
[Em]O come, let us a[D]dore Him,
[G]O come, let us a[C]dore [D]Him,
[G]Christ the [D]Lord.
{end_of_chorus}

{start_of_verse: 2}
[G]God of God, [D]light of light,
[Em]Lo, he abhors not the [D]Virgin's womb;
[G]Very God, be[C]gotten, not cre[D]a[G]ted:
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
[G]Sing, choirs of [D]angels,
[Em]Sing in exul[D]tation,
[G]Sing, all ye [C]citizens of [D]Heaven a[G]bove!
[G]Glory to [D]God,
[Em]Glory in the [D]highest:
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
[G]Yea, Lord, we [D]greet thee,
[Em]Born this happy [D]morning;
[G]Jesus, to [C]thee be [D]glory [G]given!
[G]Word of the [D]Father,
[Em]Now in flesh ap[D]pearing!
{end_of_verse}
